@@TJvSpecialProgress.Color
Description:
This is the background color of the progress bar. if the progress bar is transparent, you won't see this color.

================================================================
@@TJvSpecialProgress.EndColor
Description:
This property is the color of the progress bar. if EndColor equals StarTColor, the progress bar is painted in a unique color. if they are different, the progress bar will be a gradient.

================================================================
@@TJvSpecialProgress.HintColor

================================================================
@@TJvSpecialProgress.Maximum
Description:
Use Maximum along with the Minimum property to establish the range of possible positions a progress bar. When the process tracked by the progress bar is complete, the Value of Position should equal Maximum.

================================================================
@@TJvSpecialProgress.Minimum
Description:
Use Maximum along with the Minimum property to establish the range of possible positions a progress bar. When the process tracked by the progress bar begins, the Value of Position should equal Minimum.

