@@TJvSpecialProgress.Position
Description:
Read Position to determine how far the process tracked by the progress bar has advanced from Minimum toward Maximum. Set Position to cause the progress bar to display a position between Minimum and Maximum. For example, when the process tracked by the progress bar completes, set Position to Maximum so that it appears completely filled.

================================================================
@@TJvSpecialProgress.ShowHint

================================================================
@@TJvSpecialProgress.Solid
Description:
Specifies whether the progress bar is solid or segmented.

================================================================
@@TJvSpecialProgress.StartColor
Description:
This property is the color of the progress bar. If EndColor equals StartColor, the progress bar is painted in a unique color. if they are different, the progress bar will be a gradient.

================================================================
@@TJvSpecialProgress.Step
Description:
Set Step to specify the granularity of the progress bar. Step should reflect the size of each step in the process tracked by the progress bar, in the logical units used by the Maximum and Minimum properties. When the StepIt method is called, the Value of Position increases by Step.

================================================================
@@TJvSpecialProgress.TextCentered
Description:
if this property is true, the text is centered in the control. if this property is false, the text is centered in the painted part of the progress bar.

================================================================
@@TJvSpecialProgress.TextFont
Description:
Specifies the font used for drawing the text on the progress bar.

================================================================
@@TJvSpecialProgress.TextVisible
Description:
Specifies whether the text (percentage) is visible or not.

================================================================
@@TJvSpecialProgress.Transparent
Description:
if this property is true, the control will be transparent.

